# CELPIP Practice Platform — Project Overview

## What This Is

A Flask-based CELPIP test practice platform with Reading and Listening modules. Monolithic `app.py` with Jinja2 templates, JSON test data, and pluggable PostgreSQL/file storage.

## Architecture Quick Reference

- **Routes**: All in `app.py` (single file)
- **Test data**: `data/test_N/{skill}/partM.json` — auto-discovered, no code changes to add content
- **Storage**: Repository pattern in `utils/storage/` — factory selects DB vs file backend from `DATABASE_URL`
- **Facade**: `utils/results_tracker.py` — single public API for all user data operations
- **Auth**: Flask-Login + Authlib OAuth in `app.py` and `utils/auth.py`
- **Config**: `config.json` loaded by `config.py` — timeouts, UI settings, test metadata
- **Templates**: 13 Jinja2 templates in `templates/`
- **Media**: Listening audio/video on Cloudinary (referenced by URL in JSON)

## Stack

Python 3.9+ | Flask 3.0 | Jinja2 | PostgreSQL (psycopg2) | Authlib | Flask-Login | Gunicorn | Render.com

## Key Conventions

- Test content is data-driven JSON — never hardcode test questions in Python or templates
- `__DROPDOWN_X__` placeholders in JSON content are replaced with HTML at render time by `data_loader.py`
- Timeouts calculated dynamically: `questions × time_per_question + adjustment` from `config.json`
- Listening uses client-side JS state machine (`steps` array built in `prepare_test_data()`)
- Template selection is automatic: `skill == 'listening'` → listening templates, else reading templates
- Guest mode works without login — all features function with session-only storage

## Content Status

- Reading: 10 tests complete (40 parts, ~380 questions)
- Listening: Tests 1-10 JSON complete, only Test 1 has audio/video assets
- Writing/Speaking: Not yet started
